1 About

We computed two covariance matrices that show the relationships among individuals due to local ancestry information:

  1. GARM
    • computed as GRM on genotype data: centering & scaling applied to each local ancestry segment
    • G means that the global ancestry data vector is a part of this covariance matrix
    • PC1 on GARM = global ancestry
  2. ARM
    • computed in two steps
      • center data rows (individuals) so that the global ancestry information is removed
      • centering & scaling applied to each local ancestry segment

2 Data

2.1 Covariances

Load pre-computed covariance matrices (all chromosomes):

garm <- copdgene_garm()
arm <- copdgene_arm()

  • PC1 on ARM != global ancestry

  • PC1 on ARM = PC2 on GARM
